Analysis of the Target Image
----------------------------

1) Overall Count and Layering

•  Left “Tower” (5 pieces total):  
   –  Bottom layer: one flat green rectangular block.  
   –  Second layer: one orange cylinder resting vertically on that green block.  
   –  Third layer: another flat green rectangular block on top of the cylinder.  
   –  Fourth layer: two tall green rectangular blocks side‐by‐side above the third‐layer block.  

•  Right “Arch‐House” (7 pieces total):  
   –  Bottom layer:  
      (a) Two orange/red wedges (one on the left and one on the right).  
      (b) A central ring formed by two red arc‐blocks that fit together to make a circular hole (viewed from the front).  
   –  Second layer: two yellow half‐cylinders sitting side‐by‐side on top of the arc.  
   –  Top layer: one orange wedge forming the roof peak above the yellow half‐cylinders.  

2) Matching Blocks From the Dictionary
--------------------------------------

Based on shape, color, and the exact orientation shown in the Dictionary image (no re‐orienting allowed):

A.  Left Tower  
   •  Bottom green block: index 5 (flat green rectangular, lying horizontally).  
   •  Orange cylinder: index 9 (vertical orientation).  
   •  Middle green block (just above cylinder): index 5 again (same flat orientation).  
   •  Two tall green blocks on top: index 6 (each used twice) for vertical green rectangles.

B.  Right Arch‐House  
   •  Central ring (red) made by two halves: index 3 (left half) and index 4 (right half).  
   •  Two orange wedges at the bottom corners: for example, indices 15 and 16 (mirrored wedges).  
   •  Two yellow half‐cylinders on top: index 10 (twice, oriented flat so the curved side shows in front).  
   •  One orange wedge at the very top (roof): index 13.  

In total, you will use 12 blocks:

-  Left side: 5 blocks → (5, 9, 5, 6, 6)  
-  Right side: 7 blocks → (3, 4, 15, 16, 10, 10, 13)  

3) Suggested Assembly Order
---------------------------

Below is one logical sequence (bottom to top, left tower first, then right arch‐house).  Follow the exact block indices as chosen:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 5   // left‐tower bottom
  Step2:  Move block with index 9   // orange cylinder
  Step3:  Move block with index 5   // second green layer on cylinder
  Step4:  Move block with index 6   // left of top pair
  Step5:  Move block with index 6   // right of top pair

  Step6:  Move block with index 3   // left half of red ring
  Step7:  Move block with index 4   // right half of red ring
  Step8:  Move block with index 15  // left bottom wedge
  Step9:  Move block with index 16  // right bottom wedge
  Step10: Move block with index 10  // first yellow half‐cylinder
  Step11: Move block with index 10  // second yellow half‐cylinder
  Step12: Move block with index 13  // orange roof wedge on top
}

This completes the structure exactly as shown in the target image.
